#)What is Bean Scope?
Most common:

singleton (default)
prototype

Short answer:
“Bean scope defines how many instances of a bean Spring creates.”
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#)13. What is the difference between Singleton and Prototype scope?
“Singleton → one bean instance per application
Prototype → new instance each time it’s requested.”

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#) What is AOP (Aspect-Oriented Programming)?
“AOP allows adding cross-cutting concerns like logging, security, 
or transactions without modifying business logic.”

